Sustained by such measures, and by the renown and victories of Corbulo, the new government was no doubt winning golden opinions on every side; and it is probably to this combination of an energctic and successful foreign policy with an outwardly upright and popular home govemment, that these years of Nero owe the emphatic encomium given them by his great successor Trajan, as a period with which no other since the foundation of the principate could stand comparisont To those who study the history as we have it, such high praise is hard to justify; nor would it seem as if Tacitus meant us to regard it as more than a period in which evil tendencies were kept somewhat in check, or skilfully concealed ⁸.
